{{see|LAMP}}
==English==

===Etymology===
{{webster}}

From [[w:French language|French]][[category:French derivations]] lampe, [[w:Latin|Latin]][[Category:Latin derivations]] lampas, -adis, from [[w:Greek language|Greek]][[Category:Greek derivations]] , , (meaning [[torch]], fr. lampein to give light, to shine. Compare [[lampad]], [[lantern]].

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-æmp|-æmp]]

===Noun===
'''lamp''' (''plural:'' '''[[lamps]]''')

# A [[device]] that [[generate]]s [[heat]], [[light]] or other [[radiation]]
# A [[device]] containing [[oil]], burnt through a [[wick]] for [[illumination]]
# A [[piece]] of [[furniture]] holding one or more [[electric]] [[light]] [[bulb]]s

